snippet.textDisplay:
This song is testament to the power of coke studio signature musical genius. In this particular song the house band showcase the talented pool of musicians that they are, how they can completely transform by infusing different musical instruments and style and integrate all into one seamless up beat composition. The music director in this one manifested all that is good about coke studio and why it became such an internationally recognised musical platform raved by all over the world. Specially if you are into music and you appreciate differnt genre or  you play instruments then you will truly understand the brilliance of coke studio Pakistan. 
I will give credit to Strings for understanding and foreseeing the possibilities and potential these different talented music directors will bring. In this season 9 in every episode I am witnessing the magic of collaboration and variety of different musical styles which clearly taken the standard to a different level, set the bar even higher. The strength of the house band and their coming together has been  even more creative and brilliant. In this track the upbeat festive feel and then before the climax and end part the way guitar sets it up is stupendous. The dholak, drums and synth (brass part) was extremely catchy and when you have a bass player like munnu you can never go wrong. Finally the singers, where do I even begin. Meesha Shafi is a performer of international standard, a total diva of a singer, and the male counterpart can give Sukhvinder Singh run for his money. Overall this will end getting 5 highest viewing eventually.
